            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Need the `shell_*` message kinds to be considered non-fast.\nAnd I suppose shell output wants for `msg_show{append = true}`:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/ui.c b/src/nvim/ui.c\nindex 95889eedf9..c730631378 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/ui.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/ui.c\n@@ -785,6 +785,10 @@ void ui_call_event(char *name, Array args)\n     \"lua_error\",\n     \"lua_print\",\n     \"progress\",\n+    \"shell_cmd\",\n+    \"shell_err\",\n+    \"shell_out\",\n+    \"shell_ret\",\n     NULL,\n   };\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/os/shell.c b/src/nvim/os/shell.c\nindex 04e072908b..4a1b60569a 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/os/shell.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/os/shell.c\n@@ -1120,6 +1120,7 @@ static void out_data_append_to_screen(const char *output, size_t *count, int fd,\n   const char *p = output;\n   const char *end = output + *count;\n   msg_ext_set_kind(fd == STDERR_FILENO ? \"shell_err\" : \"shell_out\");\n+  msg_ext_append = true;\n   while (p < end) {\n     if (*p == '\\n' || *p == '\\r' || *p == TAB || *p == BELL) {\n       msg_putchar_hl((uint8_t)(*p), fd == STDERR_FILENO ? HLF_SE : HLF_SO);\n\n```",
