            "body": "I should have started with a recording. Sorry for wasting your time.\nhttps://asciinema.org/a/B7GlG4TwGeUfybK1\n\n@luukvbaal I see this on my system. Is this not related to this issue?\n\nEdit: I cherry-picked https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38715 onto master and it does give an indicator now (Like [+438]...). However, I was wondering if there is a way to see the output while it is streaming.\n\nEdit2: I can't press `g<` while the command is running because `make` is synchronous.\n\nEdit3: Motivation:\n> Streaming output is quite important for grep command IMO, so you can stop the command with Ctrl-C when it already found the result you want.\n\n(and for make too)",
